Rating: 0
Hey, if you think the apple cake featured here is tasteless, try this one. You won't be sorry! It is extremely delicious! The tangy/sweet glaze on this moist apple cake is the perfect blending of flavors. 1-1/2 cups oil, 2 cups sugar, 3 beaten eggs, 3 cups flour, 1 teaspoon baking soda, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 3 cups diced apples (McIntosh, Jonathan, Granny Smith or any tart apple). One cup chopped nuts (optional), and glaze. Combine oil and sugar. Blend in beaten eggs. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon. Add to oil and sugar mixture. Add vanilla. Add apples and nuts. Place in a greased 9 x 13 pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 300 degree oven. (Start checking for doneness after 1 hour and 10 minutes.) While cake is still warm, cover surface with glaze. Glaze: Combine 1 cup powdered sugar and juice of one lemon. Enjoy!

