Thanks to the reviewer from Rockford- I get so tired of logging on and finding comments like the one submitted by Buffalo. If we have a different opinion, why is that considered wrong? Who says yours is right, and ours is way off? Surprise surprise, this is the point of reviewing recipes- to share different points of view. If that's not what you want to hear, don't bother to log on to the rewiewing secion. To answer the question of whether or not we liked this cake, the answer is a big fat NO! It looked and smelled heavenly, but unfortunately tasted awful. It had a yucky texture, and, to justify eating a cake containing one and a half cups of oil, I think it should have been the most delicious cake I've ever baked, and it just wasn't. I've made recipes lower in fat that tasted a million times better; this was oily, and heavy, and not the autumn cake I'd serve to chase away the chills. I'm glad for those who liked it-don't berate me because I think another way!

